rComments: Her course is interesting and she take time to know her students and involve everyone in class. Attending class is important and mandatory.

shes an amazing person and an amazing prof. she explains things really well and its easy to understand the material. she has a unique way of testing (we had group tests where we did the mc test a second time with a group for 15% of the total test grade and everyone did better when it was done with a group) not too heavy courseload & easy to do well
Not a good prof
Great Professor, takes the time to ensure her students do well and always asks for feedback. Very approachable and uses the feedback in upcoming tests/lectures

Her lectures are interesting and the tests and exams are fair. Attendance isn't mandatory, but you'll lose participation points if you miss her lectures regularly. You don't need to read the textbook to do well, but I would recommend reading it to deepen your understanding of the things you may not fully grasp in class.
Amazing teacher. Engages very well with the class and always willing to help. Classes are taught in less "lecture style" and more interactive so concept learning is much easier!

At the beginning of the semester Dr. Laliberte advised the class to read assigned material prior to the lecture. The tone that she set and the way she presented herself during the first lecture (not controlling/ not demanding) encouraged me to look over the assigned readings before the weekly lectures which really helped during the semeste

Nicole is an amazing professor. If you make the effort to discuss the course material with her after class or during her office hours, her feedback will be extremely helpful. The class also requires you to take good notes during lecture. Nicole is very engaging and presents information by elaborating on key concepts and case studies.
You will never regret taking this class. She is very intelligent and brings alive a course material that could otherwise be boring. I would recommend her to everyone.

Great Professor! She really grasps the concept of allowing students to think creatively.  Most approachable professor, she actually wants to see her students do well (which is hard to find) and participate in active learning.  One of my favourite professors!
Great professor. She tried to make things understandable.  The concepts went right over my head though.  Tutorials were easy, but the marking was hard. Tests are rough.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Lots of homework', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: What a wonderful teacher. Nicole is by far one of the most amazing professors I've had thus far.

A great professor. She clearly knows what she is talking about and loves to explain it. She uses great videos, class activities and power points to help backup her points. Tests are pretty difficult. Oddly, she posts a multiple choice questions over the projector and you have 90 seconds to choose your answer.

Great Professor and great class. The lectures are clear and the information presented is useful. The assignments were designed to go out and do practical research that can also be helpful for the midterm and exam. She makes herself readily available for assistance.

One of my favourite professors at UTM. She's very passionate about the subjects that she teaches and is very engaging during her lectures. TA's were very helpful and fair in their marking. I highly recommend her courses!
Nicole is really helpful, she clarifies assignments quite well. Is patient when explaining material again to those whom have questions. Her lectures sometimes are long, but are enjoyable.

I recommend this class for all geography majors and minors. Fun course material,  the Professor makes it interesting as well as very engaging for students. Ample extra help support. A fair bit of assignment work, but they will not occupy a lot of your time.  Attendance in lectures is recommended, but it will result in a good grade.
Simply amazing! Clear and easy material. Simple tests and superb lectures. Prof Laliberte is extremely approachable and will go out of the way to help you. A must take!

Very helpful.Tried different ways of teaching to make sure students are engaged in the course. Very approachable. talk to her if you have any questions and go to her office hours. Course includes shorts papers (which aren't bad) & tutorials need participation (presentation & talking in groups). Exam not cumulative. So, great class! & great Prof!!!

Best Prof in the Geography department (or at UTM). Very helpful and enthusiastic. Lectures are interesting as every week she tries new ways of teaching to getting students interested in the course material. Fair tests. Had 2 courses with her in one semester. I highly recommend taking all of her courses. Also guys, she is pretty.
